english:
  title: Samun Island
  author: Park Ui-jung
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Dawn breaks and the morning mist disperses—
    the golden walls of the immortals' palace gleam upon the sandy shore.
    Three peaks stand like tripod legs, mountains bowing to the dawn,
    while four directions circle round with waters flowing free.

    Waves strike the stones and send up spray like snow,
    the empty pavilion catches wind and brings forth autumn's chill.
    Such boundless splendor cannot be contained in words alone—
    so I compose this verse to mark a journey to this blessed place.
  footnotes:
    - Samun Island is located off the coast of Jeolla Province in Korea. The 'immortals' palace' (仙宮) refers to the island's reputation as a place of ethereal beauty, invoking classical Chinese literary imagery of divine realms.
    - The 'three peaks' (三隅) and 'four directions' (四面) describe the island's geographical features and the surrounding seascape with poetic precision.
